				I think they removed it from the game because if an exploit someone used with it.  Group of 6 people,  all of them lvl 50: Warrior, wizz, mag, necro, sham, ench.  Enchanter Soul binded the entire group Before they attaked nagafen.  They were all bounded right near where they planned to engage negafin.   Warrior would tank,  fully buffd by ench and shaman,  while everyother class did their job.  when warrior died.  Negafin was mezmorized (by enchanter, of course) and when warrior respawned.  He got his stuff and tanked some more.    Or if wizz died,  than he re-spawns,  mems ice comet,  emties his mana load on negafin with it,  and sits and med WHILE looting corpse for int stuff.  than nuke more.  they killed negy easily with this tactic.  no casualties.  BTW if warrior didnt come back in time,  or negy resisted mezm,  than necro pet/magi pet/shaman would tank until warrior came back,  or mez worked.  Also,  the shaman/necro would fire off one last dot before they would try to mezm negy (in case warrior died)  that way negy wouldnt regain HP so fast  This is a what someone (or many people) culd do to easily gane xp and crazy high lvl loot. <BR>
<BR>
I agree that it should come back in the game.  and dialogue box would appear asking if u wanted to be bound there or not.<BR>
<BR>
-Aspin Mistwalker<BR>
Ranger of the 22nd bow<BR>
